data.chText: 几乎；差不多；事实上；实际上
data.enText: almost or very nearly, so that any slight difference is not important

data.chText: 差不多所有的学生都可免此税项。
data.enText: Virtually all students will be exempt from the tax.

data.chText: 他实际上已承认自己有罪。
data.enText: He virtually admitted he was guilty.

data.chText: 今年的结果几乎和去年的一样。
data.enText: This year's results are virtually the same as last year's.

data.chText: 模拟；虚拟；以模拟现实技术
data.enText: by the use of computer software that makes sth appear to exist; using virtual reality technology

tr: (of actions or states) slightly short of or not quite accomplished
example: the baby was almost asleep when the alarm sounded
the car all but ran her down
virtually all the parties signed the contract
I was near exhausted by the run

tr: in essence or effect but not in fact
example: the strike virtually paralyzed the city

value.def: You can use virtually to indicate that something is so nearly true that for most purposes it can be regarded as true.

example.ex: Virtually all cooking was done over coal-fired ranges...
example.tran: 差不多所有的烹饪都是在燃煤灶上进行的。

example.ex: It would have been virtually impossible to research all the information.
example.tran: 要对所有的信息进行分析研究几乎是不可能的。

value.tran: 几乎;实际上;事实上;差不多
